<h2 id="900">6. Setting up freely definable fields in the Amazon export (Seller Central)</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The freely definable fields are used to customise the data that you export to Amazon. Those fields have to be linked to <a href="/en/item/managing-items#70">free text fields</a>. The free text fields allow you to individually customise the item data and therefore save an exact description of the item.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1000">6.1. Creating free text fields</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First, create the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#70">free text fields</a> that you want to link to freely definable fields on Amazon. To do so, proceed as described below.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating free text fields:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Item » Free text fields</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name under <strong>Field name</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>data type</strong> from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the maximum number of <strong>characters</strong> for the free text field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The free text fields will be available the next day in the editing window of the items in the <strong>Fields</strong> tab. Enter the actual text there.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1100">6.2. Linking free text fields</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Once you have configured the free text fields, link them with Amazon Seller Central export fields. To do so, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking free text fields with Amazon export fields:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Amazon » Freely definable fields</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the submenu <strong>Freely definable fields in the Amazon export (Seller Central)</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-plus-square-o  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the category (<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-plus-square-o  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select an <strong>Export field</strong> from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the appropriate field from the <strong>Free text field</strong> drop-down list.<br>
→ You can only select fields that you have created.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="1200">7. Setting up freely definable fields in the Amazon export (Marketplace)</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Link freely definable fields in the Amazon export (Marketplace) for the BMVD categories Books, Music, Video and DVD.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking free text fields:</p>
